<HEADLINE>
<P>
MOVIES TO TAPE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Adventures of Sherlock Holmes (Channel 11 Wednesday at 1 a.m.): With Basil 
Rathbone as Holmes and Nigel Bruce as Dr. Watson, both perfectly cast. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Picture of Dorian Gray (Channel 5 Wednesday at 1:30 a.m.): Elegant film 
version of the Oscar Wilde novel starring Hurd Hatfield and featuring a 
delightful, very young Angela Lansbury. (2:30) 
</P>
<P>
Johnny Guitar (Channel 11 Wednesday at 3 a.m.): The Nicholas Ray cult Western 
with Joan Crawford at her most intense. (2:00) 
</P>
<P>
Kanal (Z Wednesday at 3 p.m.): The second film in Andrzej Wajda's World War II 
trilogy, it is an unsparing account of the final days of the Warsaw uprising. 
(2:00) 
</P>
<P>
The Boy Friend (TNT Wednesday at 5 p.m.): Ken Russell's stylish, engaging film 
of the '20s-era musical, starring a delectable Twiggy. (2:50) 
</P>
<P>
To Have and Have Not (Channel 5 Saturday at 3:30 a.m.): Howard Hawks' 
smoldering love story about a skipper-for-hire starring Humphrey Bogart and 
Lauren Bacall. (2:00) 
</P>
</TEXT>
