<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The U.S. Customs Service passed out $1.4 million in confiscated funds from a 
Thailand-connected drug ring to eight law enforcement agencies in San Jose. 
"This is an example of the other side of the process," said a delighted John E. 
Hensley, assistant Pacific regional commissioner for the agency. The money was 
found in bags at a Del Rey Oaks storage locker in November, 1987, and was 
packed in neat stacks of $5, $10, $20, $50 and $100 bills. The money was 
packaged by drug dealers with Southeast Asia connections, authorities said. It 
was the largest distribution of drug assets in Northern California to date. 
</P>
</TEXT>
