<HEADLINE>
<P>
GROWING PAINS FOR PARENTS, KIDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In response to "Growing Up Different" and especially to the quote by USC law 
professor Michael Shapiro: "Everyone has procreational autonomy. We don't 
require licenses for people to reproduce." 
</P>
<P>
A question: Why not? 
</P>
<P>
We require a license for marriage. Doesn't reproduction have a much greater 
effect on every aspect of society? 
</P>
<P>
VIRGINIA TAYLOR 
</P>
<P>
Granada Hills 
</P>
