<HEADLINE>
<P>
GUTS, GLORY AND THEIR EGOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Re "Guts, Glory and No Regrets" (May 10): After reading Josh Getlin's article 
on Col. David Hackworth, U.S.A.-retired, one concludes that the difference 
between Gen. George Patton and Hackworth can be summed up briefly: both had 
tremendous egos and both served their country with optimal distinction. 
However, Patton put country above ego in the final test, and that makes all the 
difference in the world. 
</P>
<P>
MICHAEL SUOZZI 
</P>
<P>
San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
