<P>
Minimum Wage 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 247 to 172, the House approved and sent to the Senate the 
conference report on legislation (HR 2) gradually raising the minimum wage from 
its present level of $3.35 an hour to $4.55 by October, 1991. President Bush 
promises to veto any hike to above $4.25, and this vote shows that the House 
probably cannot muster the two-thirds majority it needs to override a veto. 
</P>
<P>
Members voting yes want a $4.55 hourly minimum wage. 
</P>
