<P>
</P>
<P>
King Holiday Commission 
</P>
<P>
By a vote of 359 to 42, the House sent to President Bush the conference report 
on legislation (HR 1385) to begin federal funding of the commission that 
promotes the Martin Luther King Jr. national holiday. The bill sets an annual 
budget of $300,000 for the five-year-old agency, $200,000 less than the House 
authorized last month when it gave the bill initial approval by a vote of 305 
to 84. 
</P>
<P>
Members voting yes wanted to begin taxpayer support of the Martin Luther King 
Jr. Federal Holiday Commission. 
</P>
