<HEADLINE>
<P>
LIFE IN L.A. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Why does Los Angeles persist in self-flagellation? The single item that 
decreases my quality of life in L.A. is the whining of those who don't 
appreciate how fortunate they are. Those who moved here years ago from points 
east are the worst offenders. These non-travelers have the impression that 
everything "back there" has remained as they left it. 
</P>
<P>
Most people (especially those you interviewed) are unaware that the logarithmic 
increase in world population has, and will increasingly have, a degenerative 
effect on the quality of all our lives. L.A. is fortunate that it has suffered 
the least from this. 
</P>
<P>
F. H. HACK 
</P>
<P>
Torrance 
