<P>
AN UNCHANGED HEART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This is one fan who has not had a "change of heart" over the casting of Michael 
Keaton as Batman in the upcoming movie (Pat H. Broeske's "Man Behind the Mask," 
May 14). 
</P>
<P>
Keaton, as talented as he is, lacks the physical presence to make you believe 
he could intimidate criminals. Keaton isn't a wimp; he just doesn't project the 
toughness of a Sean Connery or Clint Eastwood. 
</P>
<P>
Jack Nicholson as the Joker, . . . well, maybe 15 years ago. The Joker is 
supposed to be very thin, something 'ole Jack hasn't been in a while. Also, 
let's face facts: Jack has been playing a caricature of himself for his last 
six or more films. (Think of James Woods or Willem Dafoe going all out with 
this character!) 
</P>
