<HEADLINE>
<P>
SWEDISH POLICE HOLD 15 BOMBING SUSPECTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
STOCKHOLM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Swedish police have detained 15 people of Arab extraction suspected of 
involvement in bomb attacks against a Copenhagen synagogue and airline office 
in 1985, police sources said. 
</P>
<P>
The 15 were rounded up last week by security police from different parts of 
Sweden and taken to Stockholm for questioning. 
</P>
<P>
Police said several had connections to the Popular Front for the Liberation of 
Palestine-General Command, which has been named by U.S. intelligence as being 
behind last December's bombing of a Pan Am jet in which 270 people died. 
</P>
