<HEADLINE>
<P>
HE'S LUCKY IN LOVE, LUCKY IN 'BIG SPIN' TOO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A man about to take his turn at the California Lottery's giant "Big Spin" wheel 
Saturday took a moment first to propose to his girlfriend, who was cheering him 
on from the audience. 
</P>
<P>
Steven Pack, 32, a construction worker from Ontario, slipped an engagement ring 
on Sandy Silva's finger, then spun the wheel -- to win $1 million. Pack was 
joined on the stage by Silva, who said "yes." Pack said he will use his money 
to "pay off the ring, pay for the wedding and honeymoon and start on a house 
next year." 
</P>
<P>
"Right now, it hasn't quite sunk in," he said. "I was so excited about her 
saying yes, the million hasn't sunk in." 
</P>
<P>
Pack was one of four people who became millionaires. The others were Helen 
Cunningham, 64, Long Beach; Richard Pruneau, 26, Thousand Oaks, and Norma 
Arebalos, 26, Fresno. 
</P>
