</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bill Yeoman, former Houston football coach, reached a contract settlement with 
the university, although nothing has been officially signed, the chairman of 
the university systems board of regents said. 
</P>
<P>
Yeoman is in the third year of a four-year, $412,000 contract. He was 
reassigned to the fund-raising job after the 1986 season, when the NCAA began 
investigating his football program. 
</P>
<P>
Last December, when Houston was placed on probation, a provision of the 
penalties called for Yeoman's suspension from fund-raising activities. 
</P>
