<HEADLINE>
<P>
CORONA DEL MAR BEATS MIRA COSTA TO WIN 4-A BOYS' VOLLEYBALL TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE LOWERY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Corona del Mar High School, sparked by the blocking of Jason Perkins and Chad 
Steelberg, defeated Manhattan Beach Mira Costa, 16-18, 15-12, 15-6, 15-8, in 
the Southern Section 4-A boys' volleyball championship match Saturday at Marina 
High in Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
Perkins, a 6-foot-4 middle blocker, and Steelberg, a 6-1 outside hitter, led 
Corona del Mar after it lost a draining first game. In all, Corona del Mar had 
34 stuff-blocks, including eight in the fourth game. 
</P>
<P>
Perkins was tops with 11; Steelberg had nine. 
</P>
<P>
"We really focused on our blocking," said Charlie Brande, Corona del Mar coach. 
"After that first game, we started reading their setters much better." 
</P>
<P>
Corona del Mar (16-2) had three game points in that first game but could not 
win. Mira Costa (21-1), the playoffs' No. 1-seeded team, won the game on a 
block by Zach Small. 
</P>
<P>
Matt Herrington had 22 kills for Corona del Mar, Chris Pliha 20, Matt Cwiertnia 
14 and Perkins 13. 
</P>
<P>
David Swatik had 16 kills for Mira Costa and Jason Stimpfig 14. STEVE LOWERY 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
