<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Balloons, Displays and Grape Expectations Despite enduring waits of two 
hours in an eight-mile-long traffic jam, visitors to the sixth annual Rancho 
California Balloon and Wine Festival on the shores of Lake Skinner were 
rewarded at wine-tasting booths, antique car displays and hot-air balloon races 
Saturday. The festival, which continues today, also features grape-stomping 
competitions, an arts-and-crafts show, jazz and folk music, a tribute to Elvis 
Presley and the crowning of Miss Temecula Valley. And all to celebrate what the 
Temecula Valley Chamber of Commerce calls a celebration of the valley's 
"natural resources and award-winning wineries." Admission is $3 per person 
including parking, with wine tasting an additional $6 per person. DAVID McNEW 
</P>
