</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
It's all been a joke, right? All these weeks as you've been publishing this 
pedestrian prose in your poet's corner, you've been laughing and nudging each 
other, knowing none of it could pass Emily Dickinson's definition of poetry. 
</P>
<P>
And now the denouement -- "Homage to John Cage" -- the epitome of non-poetry! 
At least Gerald Locklin has a sense of humor. 
</P>
<P>
BEA SPEARS 
</P>
<P>
SANTA MARIA 
</P>
<P>
Homage to John Cage 
</P>
