<HEADLINE>
<P>
U.S.-JAPAN FIRMS IN REFERRAL PROGRAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Oakwood Corporate Apartments, the lodging company that specializes in providing 
long-term accommodations for business travelers and corporate executives, has 
signed an agreement with Tokyo-based Asahi Homes Ltd. that calls for the two 
companies to operate a reciprocal guest-referral program. 
</P>
<P>
The deal marks Oakwood's first overseas involvement in the lodging industry. 
Terms call for the two companies to launch cooperative marketing and 
guest-referral activities designed to attract Japanese business travelers to 
Oakwood apartments in the U.S. and American business travelers to Asahi's 
lodging facilities in Japan. 
</P>
<P>
An executive of Los Angeles-based R&amp;B Management Co., the company that 
manages Oakwood's 64 U.S. facilities, said the agreement is expected to lead to 
additional transactions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
