<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Drawing, COLOR, (COVER) During Orange County's first 100 years, the postcard as 
a means of greeting has remained the same, even as the illustrations depicting 
the county have changed. But the county is embarking on its second 100 years, 
and while we cannot predict the future, we can certainly expect that the face 
of Orange County will continue to change dramatically, as will our means 
(robot-dispatched videotapes?) of saying, "Wish you were here." , Craig 
Calsbeek. 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
